{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"088e0009-d286-4583-bcef-a5f11c13d31c","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.runner.mtp` package instead:\n   ```\n   dotnet add package xunit.runner.mtp --version 0.6.1\n   ```\n   *(Use the latest version compatible with xunit 2.9.3.)*\n\n3. **Add** this property to your `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test project directly as an executable — Microsoft.Testing.Platform makes each test project a standalone app.\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n- `dotnet test` still works, but under the hood it uses the new platform instead of VSTest.\n- You can also run tests via `dotnet run` or the compiled executable directly.\n- If you use `.runsettings` files, check compatibility — MTP uses a different configuration model.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"338e5633-3dff-4b82-88a1-00b5ce481699","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge/guidance question, so I can answer directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":372,"requestId":"A04C:1BE585:17284B5:1A3F2AC:69FE8585"},"id":"9b55c370-d794-4817-9d87-e1a99b051673","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:53:34.193Z","parentId":"9280fc15-f1f7-4132-91b2-7c85611ae4e4"}
